2️⃣ Important Constitutional Facts
🔹 Constitution

Adopted: 26 November 1949

Effective from: 26 January 1950

Drafting Committee Chairman: Dr. B.R. Ambedkar

🔹 President

Head of State

Elected for 5 years

Article 52 → President of India

🔹 Prime Minister

Head of Government

Appointed by President

Leader of majority party in Lok Sabha

🔹 Parliament

Lok Sabha

Rajya Sabha

President

🔹 Fundamental Rights (Part III)

Article 14 → Right to Equality

Article 19 → Freedom

Article 21 → Right to Life

🧠 Quick Tricks (Railway Favourite)

Remember key Articles (14, 19, 21, 32)

President = Head of State

PM = Real executive

